Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm
wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the
@Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things
milder) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> Tip: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl, combine the garlic, @Panko Breadcrumbs{10%grams}, @salt{1/4%tsp}
and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British Beef Mince{240%grams}.

Season with pepper and mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> Tip: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto another #baking tray{}.

About ~{15%minutes} before the chips are ready, bake the burgers on the middle
shelf until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

Halve the @burger buns{2}.

Once cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of the burgers and pop back into
the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

At the same time, add the burger buns to the bottom shelf of the oven to warm
through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the bun bases.
Top with the cheeseburgers, then drizzle over the @burger sauce{30%grams} and
add a few @wild rocket{40%grams} leaves. Sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve the seasoned fries and the remaining rocket on the side. Drizzle the
@balsamic glaze{12%ml} over the rocket to finish.

Enjoy!